title: Geekie pair pushes Midget AAA Chiefs to win
text:
Geekie pair pushes Midget AAA Chiefs to win By: Uncredited Report Error 
Noah Geekie set up the Yellowhead Chiefs’ first goal of their Manitoba AAA Midget Hockey League game and then netted the winner in the middle frame on Friday. 
Dayton Heino opened the scoring in the first period, while Mackenzie Belinski assisted on both markers for the Chiefs (1-1-0-2) in their 2-1 win over the Southwest Cougars. Riley Lamb stopped 34 of the 35 shots he face in net. 
Carson Boyechko replied for the Cougars (1-1-0-1) early in the third but they couldn’t cap the comeback. Brady Gordon made 17 saves for Southwest.
